  </head>

<div class="container">
  <h1 class="section__headline">FAQs</h1>
  <h2 class="c-faqs__headline">General Questions</h2>
  <ul class="c-faqs">
    <li class="c-faq c-faq--active">
      <span class="c-faq__title">How do you post a ride</span>
      <div class="c-faq__answer">In order to post a ride, you first need to be logged in or create an account. Then when you're on the Post a Ride page you fill out all the necessary boxes and submit the itinerary so others can see it.</div>
    </li>
    <li class="c-faq">
      <span class="c-faq__title">How can we get in touch with people who've posted itineraries?</span>
      <div class="c-faq__answer">Once you've created an account, you can message anyone that you're interested in joining for the ride using our online chatroom.</div>
    </li>
    <li class="c-faq">
      <span class="c-faq__title">How safe is it for me to post my itinerary?</span>
      <div class="c-faq__answer">When you post your itinerary, your name and information will only be viewable by users that are logged in and have been verified. You do have the option to not have your name or any image displayed, only your username.</div>
    </li>
  </ul>  <!-- /end c-faqs -->
  
    <h2 class="c-faqs__headline">Account Related Questions</h2>
  <ul class="c-faqs">
    <li class="c-faq">
      <span class="c-faq__title">Why should I create an account?</span>
      <div class="c-faq__answer">Creating an account allows you to post rides, view full details of other's itineraries, chat with other users & create your own profile.</div>
    </li>

    <li class="c-faq">
      <span class="c-faq__title">What does a user's profile include?</span>
      <div class="c-faq__answer">Once you sign up you'll have your own user profile where you can add an image of yourself, access your chatbox, update your bio, edit your itineraries, save itineraries & get ratings/reviews.</div>
    </li>

  </ul>  <!-- /end c-faqs -->
  
</div>
